spans.text: Whose hearts stern avarice strove in vain to steel
That glows in Britain's valiant sons
rears her bloodstained banners over thy plains
Where stern Opression's hireling minions rove , To burst each tender tie of social love

Contested tenants of the peaceful breast ; Vindictive fate ruled over thy dreadful hour , When first Opression's desolating power , Deaf to the mourning parents plaintive cry , The widow's fondness or the lover's sigh , From each fond breast the hapless victims tore , Far from the prospect of their native shore
from the prospect of their native shore
From each fond breast the hapless victims
the fading flowers of fortune spring
scenes we can recall no more

Still bows submissive to the tyrant hand , That tore the sufferer from his native land ; Yet , ever the arts of luxury began , They boasted liberty , the right of man ; Serene , they saw each peaceful morning smile , Joy led their hours and plenty blessed their toil
Thou steady guide through errors devious way
